Ahead of Friday, the 29th of June, Drake has released the tracklist for his forthcoming album Scorpion. If you missed out on all that is going down in the album, click here And just as we suspected, the 25-track album has two sides. One to appeal to the rap side and the other revealing Drizzy in his R&B frame. Some songs released from the track includes God’s Plan, I’m Upset, and Nice for What.  A post shared by  champagnepapi (@champagnepapi) on Jun 28, 2018 at 9:52am PDT  We hope it addresses Pusha T’s rap diss and is worth all the hype.